{"TopicId":99127,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"PowerChute","CreatedByName":"Torquimedes","CreatedById":137645,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-08T23:12:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Torquimedes","CreatedById":137645,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-08T23:12:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EAfter using parachutes to emergency-land aircraft, and crashing some of them after forgetting to shut intakes at the same time, I wondered if it would be feasible to build a paraglider-type craft. The answer is no and yes.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003ENo, parachutes in KSP don\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00E2\u201E\u00A2t provide lift, so technically this isn\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00E2\u201E\u00A2t a paraglider.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EYes, you can build a PowerChute craft which flies with chutes deployed, in true Kerbal fashion.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EThe PowerChute One launches vertically, flies horizontally with chutes partly deployed, and lands vertically with them fully deployed.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022//imgur.com/a/VP9FP\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EJavascript is disabled. View full album\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E1. EVA before launching. Do not fall.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E2. If you fell, deploy ladder and climb to the top.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E3. Right-click the chair and board it. Engage SAS.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E4. AFTERBURNER\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E5. Above 1km, deploy chutes and pitch over.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E6. Paraglide! Or, fly a jet engine dragging a pair of chutes across the sky like anchors.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E7. When you decide where you want to land, DIVE on it steeply.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E8. At 300m the chutes will fully deploy, so cut the jet and SAS.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E9. Float to a gentle landing.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E10. Leave the chair. Hop down the landing leg.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E11. Deploy and climb the ladders to repack the chutes.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E12. Do some sightseeing and/or SCIENCE.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E13. Climb a ladder. Board the chair.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E14. AFTERBURNER\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E15. YEEEEE HAAAAAAW\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EAction groups:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E1 - deploy chutes\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E2 - toggle intakes\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EAbort - toggle intakes and reaction wheels, deploy chutes.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalx.com/Torquimedes/Powerchute\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esee Powerchute 1.4 on KerbalX.com\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-02-11T00:09:49Z\u0022 title=\u002202/11/2015 12:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 11, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Torquimedes\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ridli Scott","CreatedById":137627,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-09T14:51:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThis is the epitome of a Kerbal ship: Ingenious and hilarious.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex","CreatedById":75164,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-09T15:54:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWonderful procedure for flying! Once I get home I\u0027ll have to look at the images! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yukon0009","CreatedById":109376,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-10T09:18:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EVery nice.....but it is still essentially a jet powered rocket, as parachutes don\u0027t give lift. Wonder if 1.0 might change that.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Torquimedes","CreatedById":137645,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-11T00:09:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAdded KerbalX link to OP for the curious.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}